Colors
0: black
1: dark blue (ultramarine, azure, royal blue)
2: green (forest, kelly green)
3: teal/aqua (tiffany blue, medium turquoise)
4: red (blood red, ruby, crimson)
5: purple (dark magenta, byzantium)
6: brown (chocolate, copper, saddle brown)
7: light gray (silver, neutral gray)
8: dark gray (charcoal, ash)
9: violet/blue (periwinkle blue)
A: light green (mint, spring, pastel green)
B: light blue (aquamarine, bright cyan)
C: light red (light coral, salmon, pastel red)
D: pink (fuchsia, orchid)
E: yellow (lemon, canary, pastel yellow)
F: white

3988 - 3999 values 00 - 04?
4000 - 4011 Heights (00, 01, 02)

4012 - 5212 5 rows x 8 columns
5272 - 5381 : Name 44x5 pixels in game board


Questions:
3204 - 3267 what there?


Michalis:
Bytes:
0-827: Team name (92x18 px), 828 bytes
828-1607: team logo (30x52 px), 780 bytes 
1608-3191: Player names in team roster view (44x6 pixels, 132 bytes/player)
3192-3203: Player positions (1 byte/player, weird way, see below)
3204-3267: Player colors (not selected/selected: jersey, shorts, skin, shoes, socks, shadows)
3268-3987: Name grids on jersey (First not selected, then selected, alphabetically)
3988-3999: 
4000-4011: Player height (1 byte/player from 00 to 02, see below)
4012-5211: Player heads, alphabetically (8x5 pixels)
5212-5271:  60 bytes 12x  "40" makes all black
- even if I change the first 12 bytes everyone is black
- first 12 bytes are 00 or 01, black or white. It doesn't seem to affect the teams but it is correct.
5272-5381: Team name in game board (44x5 pixels, 110 bytes, bytes within game)


